thread.title: Saturday’s roundup: Northwestern advances to PSL final
thread.title_full: Saturday’s roundup: Northwestern advances to PSL final

author: detroitnews.com
title: Saturday’s roundup: Northwestern advances to PSL final
text:
73 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Danny Whitt threw four touchdown passes as Detroit Collegiate Prep-Northwestern rolled to a 27-8 victory over visiting Detroit Pershing in a Detroit Public School League Division 2 semifinal Saturday.
Whitt finished 10-of-15 for 135 yards and threw touchdown passes of 14 and 12 yards to Jaquez Williams and 54 yards to Calvin Fair.
Chris Dennis added 127 yards rushing on 12 carries and Rayshaun Lipscum led the defense with 12 tackles.
Northwestern (8-0) advances to face Detroit Central, a 24-20 winner over Detroit Henry Ford, in the PSL Division 2 final at 4 p.m. Friday at Ford Field.
With the loss, Pershing falls to 4-4.
More football 
Detroit Country Day 35, Muskegon Catholic Central 6: Steve Mann was 8-of-14 for 160 yards and two touchdowns and Chris Bergin had an 80-yard punt for a touchdown for Country Day (7-1).
Detroit University Prep 42, Detroit Delta Prep 12: Tyre Smith ran for 168 yards and three touchdowns and Craig Harris had 60 rushing yards, a touchdown and 12 tackles for University Prep (5-2).
Grosse Pointe Woods University Liggett 22, Sterling Heights Parkway Christian 19: Connor McCarron was 22-for-31 for 240 yards and had two total touchdowns for Liggett (6-2).
U-D Jesuit 34, Birmingham Brother Rice 0: Scott Nelson had 11 carries for 135 yards and two touchdowns and Victor Hill had a 68-yard rushing touchdown for Jesuit (5-3).
Waterford Lakes 36, Bloomfield Hills Cranbrook-Kingswood 10: Kurt Romkema had 18 carries for 172 yards and Ryan Kostich ran for 58 yards and three scores for Lakes (8-0). Tyler Santangelo was 22-of-39 for 191 yards and a touchdown for Cranbrook (7-1).
